“Substantial Modification” means modifications that materially alter the structure, core functionality, or architecture of the Software and constitute no less than 30% of the total codebase, measured by added, removed, or significantly altered lines of code. Minor edits, including but not limited to bug fixes, formatting changes, refactoring, configuration edits, renaming variables, comments, cosmetic adjustments, dependency updates, or small feature additions, do not qualify as Substantial Modifications.

